From Subject Update Back to the Moon bill Introducing the Back to the Moon in Congress The Next Step The next key hurdle for the Lunar Resources Data Purchase Act is introduction of the Act in At this point many congresspersons have been approached about the However for a successful effort to pass the bill we need the best possible congressperson to introduce the Due to his position as Chair of the House Committee on Space and Science Congressman George Brown is the logical He has a long record of support and interest in space development and helped pass the Launch Services Purchase Act and the Space Settlements There is a small group of activists in southern California who have assisted George Brown in his recent re election We are mobilizing this group to have them tell Congressman Brown about the Back to the Moon We are also asking pro space constituents to let him know that they care about getting America back to the Finally there is a good chance that a nationwide alert for space activists to call or write George Brown to have him introduce the Back to the Moon bill may be staged during late spring All this should produce a positive reaction from Brown's As more is known it will be passed However even if we are successful in getting him to support the bill this alone will not ensure passage of the For any bill to become law one of three conditions must exist either the bill must reflect widespread national support for an issue such as extension of unemployment insurance benefits be propelled by high priced lobbyists we're out of luck there or have widespread support within Congress due to small but widespread constituent The latter is the path that we by necessity must This means that the introduction of the Lunar Resources Data Purchase Act must be immediately accompanied by a large number of congresspersons' sponsorship of the To accomplish this we need activists to ask their congressperson to support the Lunar Resources Data Purchase Act To wait until the bill is introduced is simply too late it takes time to have a congressperson's staff review a If your congressperson mentions that the bill is not yet introduced please elicit their opinion of the bill as currently We appreciate all comments on the bill from activists and If you have yet to see the Back to the Moon bill please request a copy by Email please include your postal service address or contact your local chapter of the National Space Society Maximus